Greedy Algorithms: I explored the concept of making optimal choices at each step with the hope of finding a global optimum. This approach taught me to analyze problems where local optimization leads to global solutions. I tackled real-world applications, including activity selection and Huffman coding, which demonstrated the power and efficiency of greedy strategies.

Comparative Analysis: The course emphasized when to use dynamic programming versus greedy algorithms, equipping me with the knowledge to choose the most suitable approach for various problem types. This understanding is crucial in competitive programming and technical interviews.

